    "long_instructions": "### Lullaby Song\r\n\r\n**Define:** A client has asked you to make a baby lullaby using classical music that helps them go to sleep. The song should gradually lower in volume before \"fading out\" tracks one at a time.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Pick the tracks and effects you want to use and imagine what you want the timeline to look like. Consider how you want to plan the \"fade out\" effect!\r\n\r\n**Try:** Create your lullaby!\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** In order to pass this level, make sure your code has:\r\n- At least 6 tracks\r\n- At least 3 effects\r\n- A \"lowering\" volume and a fade out effect",
    "display_name": "Time to go to sleep",
